It would be great for some type of capability for a wallboard to remain functional indefinitely without a manual refresh of the wallboard to prevent a session timeout. Currently, users are displaying their wallboards within their environment through TV displays as an information radiator and would like them to display for long periods of time without any interruptions. As of now, it seems the only workaround is to increase the default session timeout but this isn't viable in some situations as this increase the session timeout for all users. Maybe there is a way to remove a session for a specific user, include a feature within JIRA to refresh the session timeout for a wallboard or enable the display of a wallboard without having to login as a user.

