h3. Problem Definition

https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver070/supported-platforms-749382629.html

A different driver version is listed in this document from the one that ships with the product. Specifically: 
{code}
2012 with the JTDS 1.2.4 driver
2008 with the JTDS 1.2.4 driver
2008 R2 with the JTDS 1.2.4 driver
{code}

h3. Suggested Solution
 
JIRA 7 now ships with the {{jtds-1.3.1.jar}}. The documentation would suggest that if a customer needs to reinstall the jtds driver, they should install the older one. This may need to be updated.

h3. Expected Behavior
Linking Stories to Epics should only require the *Link Issues* permission.

h3. Actual Behavior
If an user is not granted the *Edit Issues* permission, it will not be possible to link a Story to an Epic.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create an Epic and a Story;
# Grant *Link Issues* permission to an user and ensure they have not been granted the *Edit Issues* permission;
# Try to link the Story to the Epic;
#* If dragging the story "into the Epic" on a board
#** A permission error will appear;
#* If editing the *Epic Link* field
#** The update will look successful, but the field will not contain the Epic;

h3. Workaround
Other than granting the *Edit Issues* permission, there's no known workaround as of now.

